				\begin{document} $$V_{c}=\overline{N_{qi}}(A_{l}+A_{ns}), $$ \end{document}Vc=Nqi¯(Al+Ans), where \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$\overline {N_{qi}}$\end{document}Nqi¯ is the maximum density of infected questing nymphs within a year. Higher value of Vc means higher chance of non-systemic transmission triggered by co-feeding of infected nymphs and susceptible ticks.
